description:
Watch the 'Booth to Screen' Featurette for Zootopia 2, an upcoming Walt Disney Animation Studios film starring Ginnifer Goodwin and Jason Bateman. Don't miss the main cast in the booth for Zootopia 2, in theaters on November 26, 2025.

After cracking the biggest case in Zootopia’s history, rookie cops Judy Hopps (voice of Ginnifer Goodwin) and Nick Wilde (voice of Jason Bateman) find their partnership isn’t as solid as they thought when Chief Bogo (voice of Idris Elba) orders them to join the Partners in Crisis counseling program. But it doesn’t take long for their partnership to be put to the ultimate test when they find themselves on the twisting trail of a mystery tied to the arrival of a venomous snake in the animal metropolis. The trailer, poster and trailer stills are now available to download and share.

author: IGN
description:
My Wife Threw Out My Card Collection (So I Bought a Dump to Find Them All) is available now on Steam. Watch the My Wife Threw Out My Card Collection (So I Bought a Dump to Find Them All) launch trailer for this wacky, trash-sorting, card-collecting adventure game to see what to expect. The trailer gives a peek at what you'll do: save pigeons and other birds, find your precious cards, and rebuild your collection.

Your wife has thrown out your entire trading card collection – nothing left to do but buy a dump to get them back! My Wife Threw Out My Card Collection (So I Bought a Dump to Find Them All) makes every pile of trash a new chance to find rare cards. Dig, sort, collect your favorite cards, pull trapped birds from the garbage, and make them cozy nests in this silly sanitation sim. There are no trading card battles here, just cleaning and collecting!
title: My Wife Threw Out My Card Collection (So I Bought a Dump to Find Them All) - Official Launch Trailer

Expect bonus Mario Kart content, expert tips, and plenty of high-energy action along the way. Sponsored by Nintendo.

Tron: Ares stars Greta Lee, Sarah Desjardins, Gillian Anderson, Jared Leto, Evan Peters, Jeff Bridges, Cameron Monaghan, Jodie Turner-Smith, and more. The film is written by Jesse Wigutow, Jack Thorne, and Steven Lisberger with Joachim Rønning directing Tron: Ares.

Tron: Ares follows a highly sophisticated Program, Ares, who is sent from the digital world into the real world on a dangerous mission, marking humankind’s first encounter with A.I. beings. 

Sean Bailey, Jeffrey Silver, Justin Springer, Jared Leto, Emma Ludbrook and Steven Lisberger are the producers, with Russell Allen serving as executive producer.
title: Tron: Ares - Exclusive 'The Legacy of Tron: Easter Eggs' Clip (2025)

author: IGN
description:
Zootopia 2 picks up where the 2016 hit left off, with the first ever bunny-fox partnership in ZPD history back on the case and once again attempting to tackle systemic injustice, greed, corruption and facing one's own personal shortcomings. So of course our reviewer brought his kids along to see what they thought! 

The sequel builds off the look of the original film with a colorful palette, new terrains and ambitiously textured lighting, and, more importantly, the wall-to-wall animal puns are back in full force! But does the relentlessly hopeful Judy Hopps bite off a little more thematic weight than she can chew? 

Find out when Zootopia 2 starring Ginnifer Goodwin, Jason Bateman, Ke Huy Quan, Andy Samberg and more opens on 11/26.
title: Zootopia 2 Review

author: IGN
description:
It's a Clauster and Wang-Wasserman lawn decoration showdown in this clip from Oh. What. Fun. Check out the Oh. What. Fun. clip from this upcoming holiday comedy film starring Michelle Pfeiffer, Felicity Jones, Chloë Grace Moretz, Denis Leary, Dominic Sessa, Danielle Brooks, Devery Jacobs, Havana Rose Liu, Maude Apatow, with Jason Schwartzman with Eva Longoria and Joan Chen.

Claire Clauster (Michelle Pfeiffer) is the glue that holds her chaotic, lovable family together every holiday season. From perfectly frosted cookies to meticulously wrapped gifts, no one decks the halls quite like Claire. But this year, after planning a special outing for her family, they make a crucial mistake and leave her home alone. Fed up and feeling underappreciated, she sets off on an impromptu adventure of her own. As her family scrambles to find her, Claire discovers the unexpected magic of a Christmas gone off-script. 

Oh. What. Fun. is produced by Jane Rosenthal, Berry Welsh p.g.a., Michael Showalter,
title: Oh. What. Fun. - Official 'Lawn Inflatables' Clip (2025) Michelle Pfeiffer, Denis Leary

description:
Watch the GOAT trailer for this upcoming animated film starring Caleb McLaughlin, Gabrielle Union, Stephen Curry, Nicola Coughlan, Nick Kroll, David Harbour, Jenifer Lewis, Aaron Pierre, Patton Oswalt, Andrew Santino, Bobby Lee, Eduardo Franco, Sherry Cola, Jelly Roll, and Jennifer Hudson.

From Sony Pictures Animation, the studio behind Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse and the artists that made KPop Demon Hunters, comes GOAT, an original action-comedy set in an all-animal world. The story follows Will, a small goat with big dreams who gets a once-in-a-lifetime shot to join the pros and play roarball – a high-intensity, co-ed, full-contact sport dominated by the fastest, fiercest animals in the world. Will’s new teammates aren’t thrilled about having a little goat on their roster, but Will is determined to revolutionize the sport and prove once and for all that “smalls can ball!”

GOAT is produced by Michelle Raimo Kouyate, Rodney Rothman, Adam Rosenberg, Stephen Curry and Erick Pe
title: GOAT - Official Trailer (2026) Stephen Curry, Gabrielle Union, David Harbour

author: IGN
description:
Watch the Starbright trailer for this upcoming action/crime film starring John Rhys-Davies, Diego Boneta, Alexandra Dowling, Becky Ann Baker, and Ted Levine. The film co-stars Gbenga Akinnagbe, Tom Carey, John Westley, with Elisabeth Röhm, with Chrstine Ebersole. 

When a star falls to earth during an eclipse, Aisling (Alexandra Dowling) becomes its unlikely guardian, entrusted with the star’s fragile, living light. Hunted by dangerous men, she and Raphael (John Rhys-Davies) are saved by Joshua (Diego Boneta), whose bravery and quiet strength turn the chase into a fight for hope. Together, the three embark on a night of peril and discovery, where the light’s true gift is revealed — not in being kept, but in awakening the strength to hope and to change. 

Starbright is written by Joseph Bitonti and Olimpia Lucente. Executive producers are Olimpia Lucente and Jörg G. Neumann. Cinematography is by Francesco Di Giacomo. It is edited by Julia Furch.

Starbright opens in theaters nationwide
title: Starbright - Official Trailer (2026) John Rhys-Davies, Diego Boneta, Alexandra Dowling
